<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<chapter subject="Mathematics" id="204" name="Determinants">
    <easy>
        <question>
            <text>To every square matrix A, we can associate a number called the ____ of A.</text>
            <option id="A">Determinant</option><option id="B">Trace</option><option id="C">Inverse</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>A determinant is a scalar value associated with a square matrix.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Determinants are defined ONLY for ____ matrices.</text>
            <option id="A">Square</option><option id="B">Row</option><option id="C">Any</option><option id="D">Zero</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Non-square matrices do not have determinants.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>The value of det [[a, b], [c, d]] is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">ad - bc</option><option id="B">ac - bd</option><option id="C">ab - cd</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Standard formula for 2x2 determinant.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>A determinant of order 3 can be expanded along any of its ____ rows or columns.</text>
            <option id="A">3</option><option id="B">1</option><option id="C">9</option><option id="D">6</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Expanding along any row or column gives the same value.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If any two rows (or columns) of a determinant are identical, its value is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">0</option><option id="B">1</option><option id="C">Double</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>One of the fundamental properties of determinants.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Interchanging any two rows of a determinant multiplies its value by ____.</text>
            <option id="A">-1</option><option id="B">1</option><option id="C">0</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Each swap changes the sign of the determinant.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If each element of a row is multiplied by a constant k, the determinant is multiplied by ____.</text>
            <option id="A">k</option><option id="B">k^2</option><option id="C">1/k</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Scaling one row scales the entire determinant.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>The area of a triangle with vertices (x1, y1), (x2, y2), (x3, y3) is given by ____ * det([[x1, y1, 1], [x2, y2, 1], [x3, y3, 1]]).</text>
            <option id="A">1/2</option><option id="B">1/3</option><option id="C">1</option><option id="D">2</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Coordinate geometry application of determinants.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If the area of a triangle is zero, then the three vertices are ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Collinear</option><option id="B">Equilateral</option><option id="C">At origin</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Condition for collinearity using determinants.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>The minor of an element a_ij is a determinant obtained by deleting ____.</text>
            <option id="A">ith row and jth column</option><option id="B">ith row only</option><option id="C">jth column only</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Definition of minor M_ij.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Cofactor C_ij is related to minor M_ij by C_ij = ____ * M_ij.</text>
            <option id="A">(-1)^(i+j)</option><option id="B">(-1)^(i-j)</option><option id="C">1</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Definition of cofactor with sign.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>The sum of products of elements of any row with their corresponding cofactors is equal to ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Value of determinant (Δ)</option><option id="B">0</option><option id="C">Tr(A)</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Expansion of determinant using cofactors.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If elements of a row are multiplied with cofactors of any OTHER row, the sum is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">0</option><option id="B">Δ</option><option id="C">1</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Key theorem: Σ a_ik * C_jk = 0 for i != j.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>The adjoint of a square matrix A is the ____ of the matrix of its cofactors.</text>
            <option id="A">Transpose</option><option id="B">Inverse</option><option id="C">Trace</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Definition of adj(A).</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>For any square matrix A, A * adj(A) = ____.</text>
            <option id="A">|A| * I</option><option id="B">|A| * A</option><option id="C">I</option><option id="D">O</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Property where |A| is the determinant.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>A square matrix A is called singular if ____.</text>
            <option id="A">|A| = 0</option><option id="B">|A| != 0</option><option id="C">A is identity</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Definition of singularity.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>A square matrix A is called non-singular if ____.</text>
            <option id="A">|A| != 0</option><option id="B">|A| = 0</option><option id="C">A is diagonal</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Definition of non-singularity.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If A is non-singular, its inverse A_inv = ____ * adj(A).</text>
            <option id="A">1 / |A|</option><option id="B">|A|</option><option id="C">1</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Standard formula for matrix inverse.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>The system of equations AX = B is consistent if it has ____ solutions.</text>
            <option id="A">One or more</option><option id="B">Exactly zero</option><option id="C">Unique only</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Definition of consistency.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If |A| != 0, the system AX = B has a ____ solution.</text>
            <option id="A">Unique</option><option id="B">Infinitely many</option><option id="C">No</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Unique solution X = A_inv * B.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Cramer's Rule is used for solving ____ equations.</text>
            <option id="A">Linear</option><option id="B">Quadratic</option><option id="C">Differential</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Application of determinants to systems of equations.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>In Cramer's rule, x = ____ / Δ.</text>
            <option id="A">Δx</option><option id="B">Δy</option><option id="C">1</option><option id="D">Δ</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Δx is determinant with x-coefficients replaced.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If Δ = 0 and at least one of Δx, Δy, Δz is non-zero, the system has ____ solutions.</text>
            <option id="A">No (Inconsistent)</option><option id="B">Infinite</option><option id="C">Unique</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Condition for inconsistency.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If Δ = 0 and Δx = Δy = Δz = 0, the system may have ____ solutions.</text>
            <option id="A">Infinitely many or none</option><option id="B">Unique</option><option id="C">Always none</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Depends on specific equations (coincident planes vs parallel).</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>The determinant of an identity matrix of any order is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">1</option><option id="B">0</option><option id="C">n</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Product of diagonal elements (all 1).</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If rows and columns are interchanged, value of determinant ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Remains unchanged</option><option id="B">Changes sign</option><option id="C">Becomes zero</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>|A| = |A'|.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If any two rows of a determinant are proportional, its value is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">0</option><option id="B">1</option><option id="C">k^n</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Factor out k to get identical rows.</explanation>
        </explanation>
        <question>
            <text>det(AB) = det(A) * ____.</text>
            <option id="A">det(B)</option><option id="B">1</option><option id="C">adj(B)</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Product rule for determinants.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If A is of order n, then |kA| = ____ |A|.</text>
            <option id="A">k^n</option><option id="B">nk</option><option id="C">k</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Scalar property.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Minor M_11 of [[1, 2], [3, 4]] is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">4</option><option id="B">1</option><option id="C">2</option><option id="D">3</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Delete row 1 and column 1.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Cofactor C_12 of [[1, 2], [3, 4]] is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">-3</option><option id="B">3</option><option id="C">-2</option><option id="D">2</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>(-1)^(1+2) * M_12 = -1 * 3 = -3.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Adjoint of [[1, 2], [3, 4]] is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">[[4, -2], [-3, 1]]</option><option id="B">[[4, -3], [-2, 1]]</option><option id="C">[[1, -2], [-3, 4]]</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Cofactor matrix [[4, -3], [-2, 1]], then transpose.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>A square matrix has an inverse if and only if it is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Non-singular</option><option id="B">Singular</option><option id="C">Identity</option><option id="D">Zero</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>|A| != 0 required for 1/|A| to exist.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If |A| = 3 and |B| = 4, then |AB| is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">12</option><option id="B">7</option><option id="C">1</option><option id="D">34</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>3 * 4 = 12.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>The value of det [[1, a, b+c], [1, b, c+a], [1, c, a+b]] is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">0</option><option id="B">1</option><option id="C">a+b+c</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>C3 -> C3 + C2 makes C3 proportional to C1 (all a+b+c).</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>The determinant of a skew-symmetric matrix of ODD order is always ____.</text>
            <option id="A">0</option><option id="B">1</option><option id="C">Perfect square</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Basic property: det(A) = det(-A') = (-1)^n det(A).</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>The determinant of a skew-symmetric matrix of EVEN order is always ____.</text>
            <option id="A">A perfect square</option><option id="B">0</option><option id="C">1</option><option id="D">Negative</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Pfeiffer's property.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Differentiation of a determinant involves ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Differentiating one row at a time while others constant</option><option id="B">Differentiating every element</option><option id="C">Constants only</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Product rule analogy for determinants.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Integration of a determinant is possible only if ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Only one row consists of functions of variable</option><option id="B">All elements are constants</option><option id="C">Always possible</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Linearity of integration across one row.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If A is a square matrix of order 3, |adj A| = ____.</text>
            <option id="A">|A|^2</option><option id="B">|A|</option><option id="C">|A|^3</option><option id="D">3|A|</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>|A|^(3-1) = |A|^2.</explanation>
        </question>
    </easy>
    <medium>
        <question>
            <text>Value of det [[1, log_a b], [log_b a, 1]] is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">0</option><option id="B">1</option><option id="C">log_a b</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>1*1 - (log_a b * log_b a) = 1 - 1 = 0.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If x, y, z are in A.P., then value of det [[x+1, x+2, x+3], [x+2, x+3, x+4], [x+3, x+4, x+5]] is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">0</option><option id="B">1</option><option id="C">x</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Rows/Cols are in arithmetic progression; operations lead to zero rows.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If A = [[1, 2], [3, 4]], then A_inv is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">-1/2 * [[4, -2], [-3, 1]]</option><option id="B">1/2 * [[4, -2], [-3, 1]]</option><option id="C">[[4, -2], [-3, 1]]</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>|A| = 4-6 = -2. adj(A) is [[4, -2], [-3, 1]].</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Number of solutions of system 2x-y+3z=9, x+y+z=6, x-y+z=2 is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Unique (One)</option><option id="B">Infinite</option><option id="C">Zero</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Calculate Δ = -2 != 0.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If |A| = 0, can A be invertible?</text>
            <option id="A">No</option><option id="B">Yes</option><option id="C">Only in higher dimensions</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Singular matrices have no inverse.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If A is a 2x2 matrix such that |A| = 5, then |adj A| is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">5</option><option id="B">25</option><option id="C">1</option><option id="D">10</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>|adj A| = |A|^(2-1) = 5^1 = 5.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>The value of det [[1, ω, ω^2], [ω, ω^2, 1], [ω^2, 1, ω]] is ____ (where ω is cube root of unity).</text>
            <option id="A">0</option><option id="B">1</option><option id="C">ω</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>C1 -> C1+C2+C3 gives first column (1+ω+ω^2) = 0.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If f(x) = [[x, x^2, x^3], [1, 2x, 3x^2], [0, 2, 6x]], then f'(x) is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Sum of 3 determinants</option><option id="B">One determinant</option><option id="C">Constant</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Differentiation involves row-wise expansion.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>For any matrix A, adj(A') = ____.</text>
            <option id="A">(adj A)'</option><option id="B">adj A</option><option id="C">-adj A</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Property where taking adjoint and transpose can be swapped.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If A is non-singular, then |A_inv| = ____.</text>
            <option id="A">1 / |A|</option><option id="B">|A|</option><option id="C">1</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>From |AA_inv| = |I|.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If |A| = 2, then |A^3| is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">8</option><option id="B">6</option><option id="C">2</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>|A^n| = |A|^n, so 2^3 = 8.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>The value of det [[2, 7, 65], [3, 8, 75], [5, 9, 86]] is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">0</option><option id="B">1</option><option id="C">10</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>C3 -> C3 - 9*C2 gives [2, 3, 5], which is same as C1.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If A = [[λ, 1], [1, λ]] is singular, then λ = ____.</text>
            <option id="A">±1</option><option id="B">0</option><option id="C">1</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>λ^2 - 1 = 0 => λ = ±1.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>For symmetric matrix A, adj(A) is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Symmetric</option><option id="B">Skew-symmetric</option><option id="C">Diagonal</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Property: adj(A') = (adj A)'. Since A=A', adj(A) = (adj A)'.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>The area of triangle with vertices (a, b+c), (b, c+a), (c, a+b) is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">0</option><option id="B">abc</option><option id="C">a+b+c</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Points are collinear (calculated via determinant expansion).</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If A is 3x3 diagonal matrix diag(1, 2, 3), then |A| is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">6</option><option id="B">1</option><option id="C">0</option><option id="D">14</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Product: 1 * 2 * 3 = 6.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If |A| = 1, then A is called a ____ matrix.</text>
            <option id="A">Unimodular</option><option id="B">Orthogonal</option><option id="C">Singular</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Specific name for det=1 matrices.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Property: det(I + AB) = det(I + ____).</text>
            <option id="A">BA</option><option id="B">A</option><option id="C">B</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Sylvester's determinant identity.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If every row sum of matrix A is zero, then |A| = ____.</text>
            <option id="A">0</option><option id="B">1</option><option id="C">tr(A)</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>The vector of all 1s is an eigenvector with eigenvalue 0.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If adj(A) = B, then det(B) = ____.</text>
            <option id="A">det(A)^(n-1)</option><option id="B">det(A)</option><option id="C">1</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Basic result for second order property.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Value of det [[x, x+y, x+y+z], [2x, 3x+2y, 4x+3y+2z], [3x, 6x+3y, 10x+6y+3z]] is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">x^3</option><option id="B">0</option><option id="C">x^2</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Row operations R2 -> R2 - 2R1 and R3 -> R3 - 3R1 leads to simplification.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If α, β, γ are roots of x^3 + px + q = 0, then det [[α, β, γ], [β, γ, α], [γ, α, β]] is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">0</option><option id="B">3p</option><option id="C">q</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Expansion is -(α^3+β^3+γ^3 - 3αβγ). Sum α+β+γ = 0, so identity gives 0.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>For any square matrix A, |A.adj A| = ____.</text>
            <option id="A">|A|^n</option><option id="B">|A|</option><option id="C">1</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>|A.adj A| = ||A|I| = |A|^n |I| = |A|^n.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>The adjoint of a diagonal matrix is a ____ matrix.</text>
            <option id="A">Diagonal</option><option id="B">Zero</option><option id="C">Orthogonal</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Cofactors of off-diagonal elements are zero determinants.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If A is in row-echelon form, its determinant is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Product of diagonal elements</option><option id="B">0</option><option id="C">1</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Row echelon form is upper triangular.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>In Cramer's rule, if Δ != 0 and B = O (Homogeneous), then only ____ solution exists.</text>
            <option id="A">Trivial (All zero)</option><option id="B">Non-trivial</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Consistent system with unique solution (0,0,0).</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If det(A) = 2, find det(A_adj_A).</text>
            <option id="A">8 (for order 3)</option><option id="B">4</option><option id="C">2</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>|A|^3 = 2^3 = 8.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If row R1 of A is replaced by R1 + 3*R2, value of |A| ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Stays same</option><option id="B">Multiplies by 3</option><option id="C">Is added 3</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Invariant under R_i -> R_i + kR_j.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>A 3x3 matrix has cofactors [1, 0, 0], [0, 1, 0], [0, 0, 1]. The matrix is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Identity (or diag)</option><option id="B">Zero</option><option id="C">Skew-symmetric</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Cofactor matrix is I, so adj is I. A must be I/|A|.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Condition for non-trivial solution of AX = 0 is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">|A| = 0</option><option id="B">|A| != 0</option><option id="C">A is I</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Requires linearly dependent columns/singular matrix.</explanation>
        </question>
    </medium>
    <hard>
        <question>
            <text>If A is a non-singular matrix, then adj(adj A) = ____.</text>
            <option id="A">|A|^(n-2) * A</option><option id="B">|A|^(n-1) * A</option><option id="C">A</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Higher-order adjoint property.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>The value of det [[1, x, x^2], [1, y, y^2], [1, z, z^2]] is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">(x-y)(y-z)(z-x)</option><option id="B">(x+y)(y+z)(z+x)</option><option id="C">xyz</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Vandermonde determinant (order 3).</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If A + B + C = π, then det [[tan A, 1, 1], [1, tan B, 1], [1, 1, tan C]] = ____.</text>
            <option id="A">tan A tan B tan C - (tan A + tan B + tan C) + 2</option><option id="B">0</option><option id="C">1</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Expansion and use of tan sum identity.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If A^2 = I, then |A| can be ____.</text>
            <option id="A">1 or -1</option><option id="B">0</option><option id="C">Any number</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>|A|^2 = |I| = 1.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If A is skew-symmetric of order n, then |adj A| is ____ for odd n.</text>
            <option id="A">0</option><option id="B">1</option><option id="C">Square</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>|adj A| = |A|^(n-1) = 0^(n-1) = 0.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Jacobean matrix determinant is used for ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Change of variables in integration</option><option id="B">Finding rank</option><option id="C">Solving quadratics</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Application in multivariable calculus.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>For matrix A with entries from ring R, determinant is an element of ____.</text>
            <option id="A">R</option><option id="B">Z</option><option id="C">C</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Determinant is a polynomial in entries.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Wronskian determinant is zero if functions are ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Linearly dependent</option><option id="B">Linearly independent</option><option id="C">Constant</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Key test in differential equations.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Determinant of a Householder matrix is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">-1</option><option id="B">1</option><option id="C">0</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>It is an orthogonal reflection matrix.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If A is unitary, then |det(A)| = ____.</text>
            <option id="A">1</option><option id="B">0</option><option id="C">-1</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Complex case: conj(det A) * det A = 1.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Relation: det(exp(A)) = ____.</text>
            <option id="A">exp(trace(A))</option><option id="B">exp(|A|)</option><option id="C">|A|</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Jacobi's formula for matrix exponentiation.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>The derivative of det(A(t)) wrt t is given by ____ formula.</text>
            <option id="A">Jacobi's Formula</option><option id="B">Taylor's</option><option id="C">Leibniz</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>d|A|/dt = tr(adj(A) * dA/dt).</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Circulant matrix determinant depends on ____.</text>
            <option id="A">The first row elements</option><option id="B">Diagonal only</option><option id="C">A_11 only</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Symmetric structure simplifies to polynomial form.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If A is m x n and B is n x m with m > n, then det(AB) is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">0</option><option id="B">Product of dets</option><option id="C">Infinite</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Rank of AB cannot exceed n, so it is singular if m > n.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>The Hadamard product ____ the determinant property det(AB)=det(A)det(B).</text>
            <option id="A">Does not satisfy</option><option id="B">Satisfies</option><option id="C">Sometimes satisfies</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Hadamard product is element-wise multiplication.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Determinant of a projection matrix (A^2 = A) is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">0 or 1</option><option id="B">Always 0</option><option id="C">Always 1</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Since |A|^2 = |A|.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If A is a 3x3 matrix, find |adj(adj A)|.</text>
            <option id="A">|A|^4</option><option id="B">|A|^2</option><option id="C">|A|^8</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>|A|^((n-1)^2) = |A|^(2^2) = |A|^4.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If A is n x n, det(adj(adj...adj(A))) with k adjoints is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">|A|^((n-1)^k)</option><option id="B">|A|^(n^k)</option><option id="C">k|A|</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Generalized result for nested adjoints.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>For a positive definite matrix, the determinant is always ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Positive</option><option id="B">Zero</option><option id="C">Negative</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>All eigenvalues are positive.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If A is integer matrix with |A| = ±1, A_inv is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Integer matrix</option><option id="B">Rational only</option><option id="C">Not defined</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</explanation>Since A_inv = (1/±1) * adj(A) and adj(A) is integer.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Rank of Adjoint matrix: If Rank(A) = n-1, then Rank(adj A) = ____.</text>
            <option id="A">1</option><option id="B">0</option><option id="C">n-1</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Significant result in linear algebra.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If A has all elements from {+1, -1}, then det(A) is always divisible by ____ for n=3.</text>
            <option id="A">4</option><option id="B">2</option><option id="C">3</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Parity property of ±1 matrices.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Property of adj(kA) for matrix of order n is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">k^(n-1) * adj A</option><option id="B">k * adj A</option><option id="C">k^n * adj A</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Each cofactor involves (n-1) scaled rows.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Value of det [[1, 1, 1], [1, 1+x, 1], [1, 1, 1+y]] is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">xy</option><option id="B">1+x+y</option><option id="C">0</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Subtract R1 from R2 and R3 to get diag(1, x, y) except for top-left.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If A = [[0, a, b], [-a, 0, c], [-b, -c, 0]], then |A| is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">0</option><option id="B">abc</option><option id="C">a+b+c</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Odd order skew-symmetric matrix.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Hadamard's inequality for determinant of A states |det A| is ____ the product of lengths of columns.</text>
            <option id="A">Less than or equal to</option><option id="B">Greater than</option><option id="C">Equal to</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Geometric interpretation of volume.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Leibniz formula expresses determinant as a sum over ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Permutations</option><option id="B">Combinations</option><option id="C">Rows</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Sum signed product of entries based on symmetric group S_n.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Vandermonde determinant is non-zero if and only if ____.</text>
            <option id="A">All x_i are distinct</option><option id="B">Sum is zero</option><option id="C">All x_i are 1</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Direct result of the product formula.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Determinant of companion matrix of polynomial P(x) is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Constant term of P(x) (with sign)</option><option id="B">P(0)</option><option id="C">P(1)</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Structure links roots to coefficients.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Is it possible for x^2 to be the characteristic polynomial of some matrix A?</text>
            <option id="A">Yes (Nilpotent order 2)</option><option id="B">No</option><option id="C">Only if A is I</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Example: [[0, 1], [0, 0]].</explanation>
        </question>
    </hard>
</chapter>
